    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-06-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="263"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1448.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-06-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 10, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 25th of May, (No. 967,)
                    which is accompanied by a copy of a note of the 19th ultimo, addressed to you by
                    Earl Russell, relative to demands made by the United States on the governor of
                    the Bahamas for the extradition of Vernon Locke, has been received.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM HUNTER. <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary of State.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
